name: ANDY WARHOL: Signed U.S. Postage Stamps
description:
In 2001 the U.S. Postal Service issued a commemorative Andy Warhol self portrait stamp. One of Billy Name's portraits of Andy was printed on the selvage of the full sheet of 20 stamps.

• Limited quantity available
• Signed on the selvage by Billy Name.

name: THERMOFAX PORTFOLIO
description:
THERMOFAX PORTFOLIO: In 2008 Gerard created a new series of Thermofax prints based on the original Thermofax series he created in 1964-66 while working at Andy Warhol's Factory. An original 3M engineer who pioneered the Thernofax technology in the 1960's provided a vintage fully restored Thermofax machine and the last of his original vintage paper from 1969. With these materials Gerard created the portfolio of 8 prints, each hand signed. The lead print is numbered and features a previously unpublished poem by Gerard, written during the creation of Warhol's Death and Disaster period in the mid 1960's.

• Set of 8 prints housed in a buffered, archival box
• Each print measures 8.5 x 11"
• Since each print was produced by hand there are unique tonal variations making every example unique.
• Limited to 15 individually numbered sets.
• All 8 prints signed by Gerard Malanga

name: THERMOFAX "Andy and Gerard"
description:
THERMOFAX DELETED PRINT: The Thermofax portfolio was originally planned as a set of nine prints. During production Gerard deleted one print, a portrait of he and Andy on Gerard's first day of work at the Factory in January 1964. Only a few examples of the ninth print were produced making this an especially unique item.

• Dimensions - 8.5 x 11"
• Hand signed by Gerard Malanga
